<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
Reported as 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Macellicephala" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Macellicephala annae" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="annae">Macellicephala annae</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Chardy, Pierre" journalOrPublisher="Rapport et Proces-Verbaux des Reunions de la Commission Internationale pour l'Exploration Scientifique de la Mer Mediterranee" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="103 - 105" title="Dragages profonds en mer Ionienne- donnees preliminaires (1)" volume="22" year="1973">Chardy et al. (1973)</bibRefCitation>
from deep waters (2000-3000 m) in the Aegean and Ionian Sea, without giving a precise location. It is highly likely that the species was found in the Aegean in Greek waters, as such depths do not occur near the Turkish coast. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pettibone, M" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="1 - 71" title="Revision of the genus Macellicephala Mclntosh and the Subfamily Macellicephalinae Hartmann-Schroeder (Polychaeta: Polynoidae)" volume="229" year="1976">Pettibone (1976)</bibRefCitation>
synonymised the two species after having examined the holotype of 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Macellicephala" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Macellicephala annae" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="annae">Macellicephala annae</taxonomicName>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Arvanitidis, Christos" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Marine Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="73 - 96" title="Polychaete fauna of the Aegean Sea: inventory and new information" volume="66" year="2000">Arvanitidis (2000a)</bibRefCitation>
, accordingly, uses the name 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Bathyfauvelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bathyfauvelia affinis" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="affinis">Bathyfauvelia affinis</taxonomicName>
in his checklist. Type locality: Western Mediterranean.
</paragraph>
